<taxonomicName id="663A6E3E3F3C770F386FF18503BB98D9" authority="Schaller, 1783" authorityName="Schaller" authorityYear="1783" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterostichus (Platysma) niger" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger" subGenus="Platysma">Pterostichus (Platysma) niger (Schaller, 1783)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B0639306B1C01EBBC786882B79E9279C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="139F0AF3EB5B1F79553F32BFF10A6DAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99C4634C516B6F3027FB3921AE588392" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Europe, Turkey, Iran, the Caucasus, Central Asia, Mongolia, Siberia and the Far East (
<bibRefCitation id="F46C6440235111205217228A6AA29E17" author="Arndt, E." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Ground Beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="95C90E87471F14524B6722702D7AE3E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph id="6DB722ACCD63006ACA971E2D27F5A442" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5EAB564D561D5BAEFCE3AB1FFF0419AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
It is found in woodland, heathland and damp grassland (
<bibRefCitation id="07759C55C3B0FF3F591F0A3292530CFB" author="Luff, M." journalOrPublisher="Royal Entomological Society and the Field Studies Council" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="The Carabidae (Ground Beetles) of Britain and Ireland. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects. Vol. 4 Part 2 (2 nd Ed.)" year="2007">Luff 2007</bibRefCitation>
). It is zoophagous, thermophilous, xerophilous and an autumn breeder. It lives close to field margins and hedgerows (
<bibRefCitation id="BED32521E9002E888B1B65E98CCCEE3E" author="Thiele, H." journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin / Heidelberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Carabid Beetles in Their Environments" year="1977">Thiele 1977</bibRefCitation>
). It is common in spring planted crops and in those where minimum tillage has been practiced (
<bibRefCitation id="DDDDFBA01F8DA6E0344FD7CE4BA53871" author="Holland, J" journalOrPublisher="Integrated Pest Management Reviews" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="109 - 129" title="The Effects of Agricultural Practices on Carabidae in Temperate Agroecosystems." volume="5" year="2000">Holland and Luff 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, it was found in the cotton field in the heterogeneous area (n = 1), the cotton field in the homogeneous area (n = 15), the maize field in the heterogeneous area (n = 153), the maize field in the homogeneous area (n = 82), the olive grove in the heterogeneous area (n = 11), the wheat field in the heterogeneous area (n = 1) and the wheat field in the homogeneous area (n = 17).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
